/* 

Name: Facebook - Fixed-Position Controls
Description: Makes Facebook's sidebar and header stay fixed to the page while the rest of the content scrolls.
Tags: facebook fixed new scroll static sidebar header
Author: Cassidy James
Created: Wed, Feb 10, 2010 @ 6:03 PM CST
Last Edited: Wed, Feb 10, 2010 @ 6:36 PM CST

Current Issues:
- Does not fix the Jewel Case (Friend Requests, Messages, and Notifications buttons)
- Does not fix the top of the main content area (including the search bar, Home, Profile, and Account)
- Hides the "Switch to Facebook Lite" bar (if enabled on your account). This is for debugging.

This is a complete work in progress. Nobody related to this project will be held responsible to any damages that occur from the use of this project. It's distributed AS-IS and with no guarantee or warranty, implied or otherwise. Yay. 

*/

@namespace url(http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml);

@-moz-document domain("facebook.com") {
  #leftCol{position:fixed;/*background-color:rgb(245,245,245);*/}
  .UILiteSwitchBar {display:none;}
  #blueBar,#pageLogo {position:fixed!important;}
  /*#jewelCase{position:fixed!important;top:-4px!important;bottom:auto!important;}*/
}
